Our partner rescue organizations contact us when they identify animals in need of saving that can be helped by the Laughing Pony Rescue network.  We then act as the primary fundraiser and purchaser of these animals by making direct payments to the organizations or individuals selling them.  This is a point that can sometimes cause confusion ‚Äì while it may seem silly to pay for an animal that needs saving, that is unfortunately the way it usually works.  We are often rescuing animals from feedlots, kill pens, or auctions who expect to make a specific profit off of each animal they sell, regardless of the outcome for that animal.  In cases where we rescue animals from law enforcement agencies or humane societies, they charge a fee in order to keep their organizations running.

Check back tomorrow to learn more about the total cost of rescuing and rehabilitating the animals we save.
